# {{{1|The [[name]] of a [[god]]. (From classical Greek ''[[theos]]'' for god, ''[[nym]]'' for name) The names societies give their gods is useful at times in understanding their language as well as their view of a particular deity. Analysis of theonyms has been useful in understanding the connections of [[Indo-European]] languages, and possibly their [[religion]]s, in particular. In [[Abrahamic]] [[faith]]s the origin and meaning of the [[Tetragrammaton]] is sometimes deemed to have important historical or even metaphysical meaning. {{stub}}}}}

